      "message": "i introduced an additional goroutine here on top of what we had before (i.e. before we ran setup, test, and cleanup all in a single goroutine, now runStages creates a single goroutine but this function creates an additional one for each of setup, test, and cleanup).\n\nwe used to call the cleanup func in a defer statement (ensuring it runs even if the test func panics or calls s.Fatal), but that makes it very challenging to enforce a separate timeout on cleanup (or on closing a precondition, in the future) after the test fails.\n\nhopefully it\u0027s encapsulated enough to not complicate the rest of the code. :-)",
